imageFileName

java.lang.String imageFileName
The filename of the image, without the file format (everything before the dot). To distinguish between the images (and to not override an existing file), please make them unique by using one of the following macros: %year ... current year %month ... current month %day ... current day %hour ... current hour %minute ... current minute %second ... current seconds %millisecond ... current milliseconds %number ... number of the image in the measurement, starting at 1 %index ... index of the image (= %number-1) Everything else will be interpreted as a string. Please take care that the file name is unique and valid.
